<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->
<h3>Keep your heart healthy by including these foods to your diet</h3>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:image -->
<figure class="wp-block-image"><img src="https://static.toiimg.com/thumb/94536583.cms?width=680&amp;height=512&amp;imgsize=323938" alt=""/></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Ageing is a process that comes with a host of added changes – both in diet and lifestyle. Maintaining a proper diet and healthy lifestyle becomes of paramount importance during this period, especially for people over the age of 65, as a majority of diseases suffered by the older population are caused as a result of poor dietary choices. As the body’s metabolism and lean body mass begins its degeneration process, care must be taken to counter its affects.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Many of the diseases suffered by the elderly stem from dietary factors, many of which are due to choices made earlier in life. Some of the other issues faced by them include side effects of medication, decreased heart health, poor dental health, physical difficulty, memory loss, decreased immune function and difficulty in digestion.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>It is necessary to avoid empty calories and substitute them instead with extra, protein, calcium and other vitamins and minerals. Some of the foods that must be included in the diet plan are as follows. (Images courtesy: iStock)<a href="javascript://">READMORE</a></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->
<h3>02/3Yoghurt</h3>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:image -->
<figure class="wp-block-image"><img src="https://static.toiimg.com/thumb/94536582.cms?width=680&amp;height=512&amp;imgsize=35598" alt=""/></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>As one advances in age, their bones become weaker. In order to oppose some of these effects, it is highly crucial to have a daily intake of calcium. Yogurt is one of the best sources of calcium and must be included in the diet. This food is also rich in zinc, vitamin B, probiotics and vitamin D, which is highly crucial for a healthy heart. Additionally, keeping the weak digestive system of elderly people in mind, simple foods like yogurt that do not need to be broken down or those that can be broken down easily are suitable for them.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->
<h3>03/3Eggs</h3>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:image -->
<figure class="wp-block-image"><img src="https://static.toiimg.com/thumb/94536581.cms?width=680&amp;height=512&amp;imgsize=42894" alt=""/></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>The protein requirements of humans increase with age and eggs are the easiest and most effective source for the same. They have a multitude of benefits as they contain 13 essential vitamins and nutrients including Vitamin D as well as Choline – a macronutrient that helps in liver function, normal brain development, heart rate management, nerve function, muscle movement, maintaining healthy metabolism and maintaining muscle mass.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->
